{
  "texts": [
    "Specifically, the DMA targets large gatekeeper platforms with entrenched market power, imposing rules against self-preferencing, leveraging data advantages, and limiting interoperability and multi-homing.",
    "7 Potential clashes could arise regarding consistency in gatekeeper designations if thresholds or criteria diverge over time.",
    "Similarly, varying transparency duties and restrictions around data usage and self-preferencing might create conflicting platform obligations under each regulation.",
    "However, the regulations also align on numerous dimensions, for instance reinforcing interoperability duties and limiting behaviors constraining user choice.",
    "• The Data Governance Act (DGA) [60] passed in 2022 and applicable in September 2023, aims to facilitate data sharing in the EU by enabling data intermediaries and data altruism frameworks."
  ]
}